    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Pseudoodes subcoriaceus Chaudoir, 1882, holotype. A: habitus and labels of holotype; B: head and pronotum; C: mentum; D: prosternal process; E: right metepisternum and metacoxa (arrow shows lateral end of metacoxal basal sulcus). Scale lines = 2 mm (Fig. A); = 1 mm (Figs B–E)." ;
